1
00:01:38,599 --> 00:01:39,439
I promise

2
00:01:41,239 --> 00:01:42,680
I'll never make you cry again

3
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:04,159
Get some sleep

4
00:02:27,919 --> 00:02:28,759
Marry me

5
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:03,479
I mean it

6
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:36,520
Stop crowding around me

7
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:37,680
It feels weird

8
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:38,800
Let me catch my breath

9
00:03:39,599 --> 00:03:40,439
No way

10
00:03:40,719 --> 00:03:42,159
You have to hear what everyone

11
00:03:42,159 --> 00:03:43,439
what everyone really thinks

12
00:03:43,439 --> 00:03:44,199
Exactly, right?

13
00:03:44,479 --> 00:03:45,080
Right

14
00:03:46,199 --> 00:03:48,120
Deputy Yi, you have no idea

15
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:49,400
While you were away

16
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:51,439
we realized just how important you are

17
00:03:51,439 --> 00:03:53,439
The place was like a ship without a captain

18
00:03:53,439 --> 00:03:54,000
Exactly

19
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:54,439
That's right

20
00:03:54,439 --> 00:03:56,759
Honestly, none of us believed

21
00:03:56,759 --> 00:03:58,120
any of that nonsense, right?

22
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:58,599
Right

23
00:03:58,599 --> 00:04:00,280
Those rumors were obviously fake

24
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:02,080
Anyone with a brain wouldn't buy it

25
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:03,680
We all believe in you

26
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:03,919
Right

27
00:04:03,919 --> 00:04:04,960
Listen to me

28
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:06,080
Just focus on rehearsing

29
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:07,719
and put your mind at ease

30
00:04:07,719 --> 00:04:09,080
As for Chu Jiahe,

31
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:10,599
she's already confessed to the leadership

32
00:04:10,599 --> 00:04:11,560
Confessed what?

33
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:13,039
Confessed to spreading rumors

34
00:04:13,039 --> 00:04:14,800
She said she made it all up

35
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:16,399
She's been jealous of you since childhood

36
00:04:16,399 --> 00:04:17,639
She can't stand seeing you do well

37
00:04:17,639 --> 00:04:18,720
So she did everything she could

38
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:20,160
to drag your name through the mud

39
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,160
Don't, don't listen to him

40
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:23,480
Only your first sentence was true

41
00:04:23,480 --> 00:04:25,160
The rest is just embellishment

42
00:04:27,839 --> 00:04:30,199
A lot has happened during this time

43
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:32,480
Let's all learn a lesson from it

44
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:34,879
Don't jump to conclusions next time

45
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:37,120
But for now,

46
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:38,879
the most important thing for us

47
00:04:38,879 --> 00:04:40,240
is to get back on track

48
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:41,839
and start rehearsing right away

49
00:04:41,839 --> 00:04:43,360
Time waits for no one

50
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:44,519
Right?

51
00:04:45,079 --> 00:04:46,839
Come on, let's start

52
00:04:46,839 --> 00:04:47,240
Okay

53
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:48,360
Come on, come on

54
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:49,519
Rehearse, rehearse, rehearse

55
00:04:49,519 --> 00:04:51,279
Hurry, hurry, no time to waste

56
00:04:53,519 --> 00:04:54,040
Director

57
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:56,959
Qin'e

58
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:58,480
Come here

59
00:05:05,759 --> 00:05:07,079
I hear you're getting married

60
00:05:10,759 --> 00:05:11,680
Congratulations

61
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,839
Young Liu is a good man

62
00:05:14,079 --> 00:05:15,079
Worth committing to

63
00:05:15,480 --> 00:05:16,560
Thank you, Director

64
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:19,920
I have something I want to tell you

65
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,199
Once you're married,

66
00:05:21,439 --> 00:05:23,920
don't have a child for three to five years

67
00:05:24,399 --> 00:05:27,240
That's, that's not even on my agenda yet

68
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:28,519
By the time it is,

69
00:05:28,519 --> 00:05:29,879
I'll be done for here

70
00:05:30,399 --> 00:05:31,519
Think about it, in this whole troupe,

71
00:05:31,519 --> 00:05:34,120
how hard it is to train performers like you

72
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:36,120
Chu Jiahe wants to leave

73
00:05:36,120 --> 00:05:36,680
You see?

74
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:38,639
What's the troupe supposed to do?

75
00:05:38,639 --> 00:05:40,360
We'd be left putting on monk plays

76
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,560
Chu Jiahe wants to leave

77
00:05:42,759 --> 00:05:43,879
She's already submitted her request

78
00:05:43,879 --> 00:05:44,519
It's in my office

79
00:05:44,519 --> 00:05:45,759
I haven't approved it yet

80
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,000
Who is it?

81
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,519
It's me, Yi Qin'e

82
00:06:04,079 --> 00:06:04,920
What are you doing here?

83
00:06:05,279 --> 00:06:06,639
Why aren't you performing anymore?

84
00:06:07,839 --> 00:06:09,240
I'm not part of your youth troupe.

85
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:09,879
It's none of your business.

86
00:06:10,439 --> 00:06:10,920
Regardless,

87
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:11,480
I still hope you'll

88
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:13,000
finish Beating Jiao Zan before leaving.

89
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,079
What's it got to do with you?

90
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:19,040
I know it wasn't you.

91
00:06:19,639 --> 00:06:20,800
No matter how much you hate or resent me,

92
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:22,160
you wouldn't do something like that.

93
00:06:25,519 --> 00:06:26,439
How do you know?

94
00:06:27,199 --> 00:06:27,959
If you'd done it,

95
00:06:27,959 --> 00:06:29,199
you wouldn't have saved me.

96
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:37,160
Ms. Mi Lan came to see me.

97
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:39,759
What did she say?

98
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:43,600
She said,

99
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:46,360
everyone wants to be the lead,

100
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:48,439
but most people

101
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:50,040
end up playing extras.

102
00:06:51,639 --> 00:06:53,399
Once you see yourself as a spectator,

103
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:55,399
you'll find

104
00:06:55,399 --> 00:06:56,879
everything becomes much easier.

105
00:07:01,439 --> 00:07:02,800
After all this time,

106
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:06,600
I've realized I'm nothing but a spectator.

107
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:11,720
Right time, right place, right people,

108
00:07:12,759 --> 00:07:13,879
all of them aligned,

109
00:07:14,519 --> 00:07:15,800
that's what it takes to be the lead.

110
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:18,879
Why?

111
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,319
Why is it that none of those things,

112
00:07:21,319 --> 00:07:22,800
ever fall in my favor?

113
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:26,000
I only get what you don't want.

114
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:31,000
Saying I'm not as good as you,

115
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,240
I won't accept that.

116
00:07:34,079 --> 00:07:35,439
No matter what, I won't accept it.

117
00:07:37,319 --> 00:07:38,759
You're just luckier than me.

118
00:07:42,199 --> 00:07:44,160
Actually, being the lead on stage,

119
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:47,240
doesn't mean you're the lead in life.

120
00:07:48,439 --> 00:07:49,600
Sometimes,

121
00:07:50,279 --> 00:07:51,879
the more brilliant you are on stage,

122
00:07:52,959 --> 00:07:54,800
the more empty you feel after.

123
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:59,160
I'd love to experience that emptiness for once.

124
00:08:00,639 --> 00:08:02,040
Then finish performing Beating Jiao Zan.

125
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:05,199
Finish it, and you'll have no regrets after.

126
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:10,680
These days,

127
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:12,399
have been rough on you, haven't they?

128
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:16,920
What about you?

129
00:08:19,079 --> 00:08:20,480
People will say what they want.

130
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:22,600
I can't control what they say.

131
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:24,639
In this whole thing,

132
00:08:25,319 --> 00:08:26,920
someone has to suffer.

133
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:28,439
If it's not you,

134
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:30,040
then it's me.

135
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:32,679
Fortunes change, after all.

136
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:38,279
So,

137
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:39,799
it's a deal then.

138
00:08:40,559 --> 00:08:41,919
You finish Beating Jiao Zan,

139
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:43,200
and I'll perform The Fox Immortal's Tribulation.

140
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:45,480
The two of us will make a real splash together.

141
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:54,840
Bingbing

142
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:55,919
Come, come, come

143
00:08:56,120 --> 00:08:56,879
Brother-in-law

144
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,279
Slow, slow down, slow down

145
00:08:58,720 --> 00:08:59,799
Brother-in-law, what's all this?

146
00:08:59,799 --> 00:09:00,799
Why's it so heavy?

147
00:09:00,799 --> 00:09:03,039
Good stuff you can't get in the city

148
00:09:03,039 --> 00:09:03,679
Uncle, Auntie

149
00:09:03,679 --> 00:09:04,720
Bingbing

150
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:05,840
Why haven't you changed how you address us?

151
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:06,720
Still calling us Uncle and Auntie

152
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:07,759
Something this important

153
00:09:07,759 --> 00:09:09,799
Has to wait till the wedding day

154
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:11,679
I'll call out and make you both happy

155
00:09:11,679 --> 00:09:14,200
See how thoughtful Bingbing is

156
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:14,759
Let's go, let's go

157
00:09:14,759 --> 00:09:15,399
Liu Hongbing

158
00:09:15,879 --> 00:09:16,679
Where's Laidi?

159
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:19,159
She and Uncle are still rehearsing at the troupe

160
00:09:19,159 --> 00:09:20,279
I'll take you to a hotel

161
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:22,000
Why stay at a hotel?

162
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:24,159
Laidi and her uncle both have places

163
00:09:24,159 --> 00:09:25,519
We'll just stay there

164
00:09:25,879 --> 00:09:27,080
It's such a small thing

165
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:29,120
Now that you're here, let the kid arrange it

166
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:30,000
I'll go along with thoughtful gestures

167
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,519
But spending money? Not happening

168
00:09:31,919 --> 00:09:33,120
Here, take it, pack it up

169
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:33,720
Here, Mom, Mom

170
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:34,480
Mom, stop fussing

171
00:09:36,639 --> 00:09:37,320
Brother

172
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:38,360
Here, want some water?

173
00:09:38,879 --> 00:09:40,600
Brother-in-law, can I play this game console?

174
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:41,600
Sure, go ahead

175
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:42,240
Of course

176
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:44,039
Just plug in this cartridge

177
00:09:44,039 --> 00:09:44,799
The TV's not on

178
00:09:44,799 --> 00:09:45,039
Bingbing

179
00:09:45,039 --> 00:09:46,000
What are you playing?

180
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:46,480
Bingbing

181
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:47,039
I had a look around

182
00:09:47,039 --> 00:09:47,519
Auntie

183
00:09:47,519 --> 00:09:49,840
Laidi, Pandi, and I will sleep in the big room

184
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:51,679
You and Dad take the small room

185
00:09:52,120 --> 00:09:52,840
Cungen

186
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:54,159
You and your brother-in-law

187
00:09:54,159 --> 00:09:56,039
Just lay out a bedroll here on the floor

188
00:09:56,159 --> 00:09:57,519
Why sleep on the floor?

189
00:09:57,519 --> 00:09:59,240
Just get a room at the Beishan Inn

190
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:01,240
A room costs money, doesn't it?

191
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:02,759
Save what we can

192
00:10:02,759 --> 00:10:03,480
Listen to me

193
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:04,360
I'm not going anywhere

194
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,360
I'm staying with my brother-in-law

195
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:05,960
You silly thing

196
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:09,039
Fine, I'll bunk on the floor with you

197
00:10:09,039 --> 00:10:09,799
Hongbing

198
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:12,879
Hongbing, this string's way too thin

199
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:14,480
Flushing the toilet, I, I...

200
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:15,639
A light tug and it snapped

201
00:10:15,639 --> 00:10:17,080
Find a thicker one, I'll swap it out

202
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:18,679
Uncle, don't worry about it

203
00:10:18,679 --> 00:10:20,399
That lousy string's been broken for ages

204
00:10:20,399 --> 00:10:20,600
Well...

205
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:21,519
I've been meaning to replace it

206
00:10:21,519 --> 00:10:22,320
Just use it for now

207
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:22,519
Well, well...

208
00:10:22,519 --> 00:10:23,559
I'll change it out tomorrow

209
00:10:23,559 --> 00:10:25,639
Brother-in-law, where do I put this?

210
00:10:25,639 --> 00:10:26,440
Sis, what's all this?

211
00:10:26,440 --> 00:10:27,360
Herbal medicine

212
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:29,759
Your brother-in-law and I got it for Laidi

213
00:10:29,759 --> 00:10:30,960
Thanks, brother-in-law

214
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:31,840
Brother-in-law, Sis

215
00:10:32,559 --> 00:10:33,200
Wonderful

216
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:33,440
Good, good, good

217
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:34,120
Bingbing

218
00:10:34,519 --> 00:10:35,080
Coming, coming, coming

219
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:36,799
Where are your pillows and blankets?

220
00:10:37,759 --> 00:10:39,799
Brother-in-law, why can't I get past this level?

221
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:40,440
Brother-in-law

222
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:41,120
I'll be right there

223
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:42,039
Okay, okay, I'll figure it out myself

224
00:10:42,039 --> 00:10:42,799
Brother-in-law

225
00:10:43,759 --> 00:10:45,080
What's so hard to get past?

226
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:47,080
Every level is tough, but you'll beat it.

227
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:48,919
Come on, come on

228
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:51,720
The wedding banquet is on the tenth next month

229
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:52,879
At Chang'an Restaurant

230
00:10:53,639 --> 00:10:55,200
We hired a famous Cantonese chef

231
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:57,360
Plenty of fresh seafood, all you can eat

232
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:58,840
Great

233
00:10:59,679 --> 00:11:01,279
Last year when Wang Qinsheng got married

234
00:11:01,279 --> 00:11:03,000
There wasn't even a scrap of meat at the banquet

235
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:04,559
Just a whole table of green vegetables

236
00:11:04,559 --> 00:11:05,399
Isn't he afraid that one day

237
00:11:05,399 --> 00:11:06,559
He'll end up wearing a green hat himself?

238
00:11:09,159 --> 00:11:09,799
Director

239
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:10,919
Here, have a cigarette

240
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:15,679
Wishing you both happiness!

241
00:11:16,639 --> 00:11:17,840
Her voice is cracking.

242
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:21,039
Beating Jiao Zan, half price!

243
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:24,039
Beating Jiao Zan, half price!

244
00:11:24,559 --> 00:11:26,320
Half-price tickets! Half-price tickets!

245
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:27,120
Who wants one?

246
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:28,679
Half-price tickets!

247
00:11:29,039 --> 00:11:30,840
Any tickets left for The Fox Immortal's Tribulation?

248
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:31,919
What are you thinking?

249
00:11:31,919 --> 00:11:33,519
Those sold out ages ago.

250
00:11:33,519 --> 00:11:34,600
Want Beating Jiao Zan?

251
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:35,600
No.

252
00:11:36,519 --> 00:11:38,360
It's not as good as The Fox Immortal's Tribulation.

253
00:11:47,000 --> 00:12:04,360
The Marshal's Command.

254
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:26,679
You hit the kid's head.

255
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:00,399
You sing so beautifully.

256
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:03,679
You really mean that?

257
00:13:06,919 --> 00:13:09,039
But this role really doesn't suit you.

258
00:13:09,559 --> 00:13:11,360
You're no kitchen maid.

259
00:13:11,759 --> 00:13:13,879
You're Cui Yingying.

260
00:13:14,279 --> 00:13:15,600
You're Princess Shengping.

261
00:13:16,639 --> 00:13:18,440
You'll never know suffering in your life.

262
00:13:20,879 --> 00:13:22,440
I heard you're getting married.

263
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:27,200
Congratulations.

264
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:30,200
Thank you.

265
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,080
Can you come?

266
00:13:33,639 --> 00:13:34,879
To our wedding.

267
00:13:35,879 --> 00:13:37,440
I'm leaving the day after tomorrow.

268
00:13:38,440 --> 00:13:39,279
For Shenzhen.

269
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:41,480
I'm not coming back.

270
00:13:42,799 --> 00:13:44,120
Shenzhen.

271
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:46,360
That's so far away.

272
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:50,600
I'm going to be the lead of my own life.

273
00:13:52,679 --> 00:13:53,600
Yi Qin'e.

274
00:13:57,679 --> 00:13:58,960
You must be happy from now on.

275
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:04,200
We'll all be happy.

276
00:14:23,559 --> 00:14:25,360
After the show ended that night,

277
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:27,399
Chu Jiahe, all alone,

278
00:14:27,399 --> 00:14:29,600
stood on the stage for a long time.

279
00:14:30,879 --> 00:14:33,039
Thinking of her days on the stage,

280
00:14:33,360 --> 00:14:35,399
of all she'd laughed and cried,

281
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:39,320
of the tears and sweat she'd shed.

282
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:42,799
But Chu Jiahe decided to let it go.

283
00:14:43,840 --> 00:14:46,399
She understood sooner than Yi Qin'e:

284
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:49,240
no show in life lasts forever.

285
00:14:49,879 --> 00:14:51,679
Knowing when to lower your own curtain

286
00:14:52,159 --> 00:14:54,200
is what makes a true star performer.

287
00:15:21,159 --> 00:15:28,360
This mortal world

288
00:15:28,759 --> 00:15:36,399
has wronged me,

289
00:15:36,399 --> 00:15:47,360
